it.polimi.se2019.util

Class Response

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.se2019.util.Response
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NetMsg, java.io.Serializable

    public class Response
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, NetMsg
    The Response class is the network object that is sent from server to client for any kind of notification and communitation. It can contain a game for match initialization or a list of updates. It always carries a String message, which can be used by the server to send view selection messages.
    Author:
    andreahuang

      • Response

        public Response(Game game,
                boolean success,
                java.lang.String message)
        Default constructor. It sets up the parameters for match initialization or message selection for the String message.
        Parameters:
        game - the initialized game, if present
        success - is boolean parameter used to call the showMessage method or the reportError method on the client.
        message - is selection message when success is true, an error message otherwise.

        Parameters:
